CADI.Common.Cache

Class ImplicitBinDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • CADI.Common.Cache.ImplicitBinDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClassIdentifiers

    public class ImplicitBinDescriptor
extends java.lang.Object
implements ClassIdentifiers
    This class is used as a container for the implicit-bin-descriptor.

    Information about data-bins can be set using the numberOfLayers attribute.

    Regarding the ranges (first and last attributes) are both BinDescriptor.WILDCARD it means a wilcard.

    The meaning of numberOfLayers is a wildcard if is BinDescriptor.WILDCARD.

    Further information, see ISO/IEC 15444-9 sect. C.8.1.3

    Version:
    1.0.1 2011/03/06
    Author:
    Group on Interactive Coding of Images (GICI)
